        <mxCell id="xqdrlZmtMru8qiV6mRAN-4" parent="DNa5gxV0blv_Pn_uQVtT-20" style="rounded=1;whiteSpace=wrap;html=1;fontStyle=1;fontSize=23;fillColor=#eeeeee;strokeColor=#36393d;fontColor=default;labelBackgroundColor=none;arcSize=4;align=center;container=0;" value="InfraContainer is an object that holds all registered implementations of various ports. Regular attributes (like the main pipeline components) are stored as sequences (Sequence[Implementations]). Helpers, however, are stored in a dictionary (Dict[str, Sequence[Implementations]]). The container does not store instances — it stores implementation classes. Instances are created on demand based on which implementation is selected. Helpers are kept in a dictionary to allow the Assembler to quickly locate them, regardless of whether their attributes are registered. This also helps separate helper objects from the main pipeline objects." vertex="1">
